MIRAE

未来 / 미래
The future of streaming.

WHAT IS MIRAE?

Mirae is a modern Korean-drama streaming UI built with:

- SvelteKit (Svelte 5, runes)
- Bun (runtime + package manager)
- TypeScript
- Tailwind CSS v4 (token-driven design system)
- Firebase Auth
- TMDB (server-side only)

Focused on speed, immersion, and cinematic browsing,
Mirae delivers a smooth OTT-style experience inspired by modern streaming platforms.

FEATURES

- cinematic homepage with auto-playing background trailer
- guest mode (static cards) vs authenticated mode (full interaction)
- TMDB-powered Korean-drama discovery (popular, trending, top rated, new releases, genre rows)
- hover-preview cards with trailer playback
- show-details modal with similar titles
- My List with localStorage persistence per Firebase uid
- Firebase Auth flow: login, signup, forgot password, password reset
- responsive layout (640 / 768 / 1024 breakpoints)
- mobile menu, sticky navbar, profile dropdown
- dark cinematic UI aesthetics

TECH STACK

Frontend

- SvelteKit + Svelte 5 runes
- TypeScript (strict)
- Tailwind CSS v4 (with custom @theme tokens in src/app.css)
- @lucide/svelte for icons
- Plyr for the video player

Runtime / Deploy

- Bun for dev, build, install
- Vercel for production deployment via @sveltejs/adapter-vercel

APIs

- TMDB (server only, never called from the browser)
- YouTube trailers (embedded via Plyr)
- Firebase Auth (client SDK)

PROJECT STRUCTURE

src/
├── app.css - Tailwind v4 entry + @theme tokens
├── lib/
│ ├── constants.ts - Shared constants (TMDB paths, storage keys, route arrays, timings)
│ ├── helpers.ts - Pure helpers (tmdbImage, matchPercent, releaseYear, fetchTrailer, ...)
│ ├── firebase.ts - Firebase init + authErrorMessage()
│ ├── utils.ts - cn() classname merger
│ ├── components/
│ │ ├── \*.svelte - Feature components (Billboard, ContentRow, Thumbnail, ...)
│ │ ├── auth/ - Login/signup form primitives
│ │ ├── profile/ - Avatar, ProfileDropdown
│ │ └── ui/ - shadcn-svelte primitives (bits-ui based)
│ ├── fixtures/ - Mock seed data (e.g. MOCK_ACCOUNT)
│ ├── server/api/ - TMDB client (server-only)
│ ├── stores/ - Class-based runes stores with createContext<T>() pairs
│ └── types/ - Ambient .d.ts files (Movie, Account, TrackedDevice, ...)
└── routes/
├── +layout.svelte - Auth guard, store wiring, layout chrome
├── +page.{svelte,server.ts}- Home: billboard + curated rows
├── (auth)/ - Login / signup / forgot / reset
├── account/ - Account/settings page
├── myList/ - User's favorites
├── search/ - Search results
├── watch/[movieId]/ - Trailer player
└── api/ - Internal proxies to TMDB (movie, similar, trailer)

DEVELOPMENT

Install dependencies:

bun install

Set TMDB + Firebase keys in .env (see .env.example):

TMDB_API_KEY=...
PUBLIC_FIREBASE_API_KEY=...
PUBLIC_FIREBASE_AUTH_DOMAIN=...
PUBLIC_FIREBASE_PROJECT_ID=...
PUBLIC_FIREBASE_APP_ID=...

Run the dev server:

bun run dev

COMMANDS

bun dev Start dev server (Vite)
bun run build Production build (emits Vercel adapter output)
bun preview Preview the production build locally
bun check svelte-kit sync && svelte-check
bun check:watch svelte-check --watch
bun lint prettier --check + eslint
bun format prettier --write

DEPLOYMENT (VERCEL)

1. Push the repo to GitHub.
2. Import on Vercel — SvelteKit + Bun are auto-detected from bun.lock.
3. Set env vars on Vercel for Production / Preview / Development:
   TMDB_API_KEY, PUBLIC_FIREBASE_API_KEY, PUBLIC_FIREBASE_AUTH_DOMAIN,
   PUBLIC_FIREBASE_PROJECT_ID, PUBLIC_FIREBASE_APP_ID
4. Add the Vercel domain to Firebase Console → Authentication → Authorized domains.

No vercel.json required — @sveltejs/adapter-vercel handles the function output.

DESIGN PHILOSOPHY

Mirae is built around three ideas:

- speed
- simplicity
- immersion

Minimal UI noise. Fast interactions. Cinematic presentation.

